node.text: While many events have had to be cancelled this year, trans actor, writer and director @jake_graf5 shows us how him and his family are still celebrating Pride at home. How lovely do they all look in our #FeelingProud collection?! 💜  This year, we’re proud to continue to support @ilgaworld with a £150,000 donation, helping in their mission for LGBTQI+ equality. Head to primark.com to find out more #Primark #PrideMonth

Head to primark.com to find out more #Primark

node.text: This month on #PrimarkSpotlight, we meet the incredibly talented singer/songwriter @iamkyami. Originally from New York, Kyami has lived in the UK for three and a half years and currently writes, produces, performs and DJs (just to name a few). Kyami chats to us about finding empowerment within her true sound and pushing through failures to find successes. On a chilled Friday vibe? Make sure you go and check out 'IAmKyami' on Spotfiy for the ultimate soundtrack to match your mood ✨ #Primark #FeelGoodFriday

node.text: This month, we meet the lovely @dani_durrett, an amazing artist with the Boston Ballet. Not only does Daniel's talent shine through, but his determination, positivity and drive to succeed, no matter the obstacle, has got us feeling motivated to go and smash the next goal. Feeling like dance could be for you? Daniel says 'dance is for everyone - just put some music on and let your body do the talking' and we couldn't love that phrase more. Was lovely to meet you, Daniel! Thanks for reminding us to never give up on our goals 🙌 #PrimarkSpotlight
